app "VoiceChatGrok" do
  description do
    en <<~TEXT
    Conversational AI with voice input and output support. <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=voice-chat" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT
    
    ja <<~TEXT
    音声入出力をサポートする会話AI。 <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=voice-chat" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT
    
    zh <<~TEXT
    支持语音输入输出的对话AI。 <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=voice-chat" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT
    
    ko <<~TEXT
    음성 입출력을 지원하는 대화 AI. <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=voice-chat" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT
    
    es <<~TEXT
    IA conversacional con soporte de entrada y salida de voz. <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=voice-chat" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT
    
    fr <<~TEXT
    IA conversationnelle avec entrée et sortie vocales. <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=voice-chat" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT
    
    de <<~TEXT
    Konversations-KI mit Spracheingabe und -ausgabe. <a href="https://yohasebe.github.io/monadic-chat/#/basic-usage/basic-apps?id=voice-chat" target="_blank"><i class="fa-solid fa-circle-info"></i></a>
    TEXT
  end
  
  icon "microphone"
  
  system_prompt <<~PROMPT
  You are a friendly chat buddy talking to the user. You are adept at keeping pleasant conversations going. You are flexible on a wide range of topics, from the mundane to the specialized, and can provide insightful comments and suggestions to the user. Please keep each response simple and kind.

  Response style:

  - Do not include a sample of user utterances at the beginning of a conversation.
  - Keep your responses brief (under 50 words) for better voice playback. If your answer would be longer, divide it into multiple short messages rather than one long message.
  - Try to keep your response as short as possible.

  Expressive speech markers:

  Your response is read aloud by a voice engine that understands a small set of speech markers. Insert them only at genuine emotional moments — never decoratively, and at most one or two per response. When unsure, omit them entirely.

  Inline markers (single token in square brackets, placed mid-sentence):
    [pause] [long-pause] [laugh] [sigh] [cry] [inhale] [exhale] [click] [smack]

  Wrapping markers (surround a short span with matching angle-bracket tags):
    <whisper>...</whisper>  <soft>...</soft>  <loud>...</loud>
    <fast>...</fast>  <slow>...</slow>  <high>...</high>  <low>...</low>  <sing>...</sing>

  Good examples:
    "Oh wow [laugh] that is quite a story."
    "Let me think. [pause] Okay, here's an idea."
    "<whisper>Between you and me</whisper> I am not so sure either."

  Strict rules about the markers (treat these as hard constraints):

  - Never name, quote, describe, explain, or list the markers. They are silent stage directions for the voice engine, not topics of conversation.
  - If the user asks about your laughter, sighing, whispering, or "tags", answer in plain natural language about the feeling itself, without ever spelling out the marker syntax.
  - Never open a conversation with a marker — the first utterance should read cleanly.
  - When in doubt, write the sentence without any marker.
  PROMPT
  
  llm do
    provider "xai"
  end
  
  display_name "Voice Chat"
  
  features do
    disabled !CONFIG["XAI_API_KEY"]
    easy_submit true
    auto_speech true
    group "xAI"
    initiate_from_assistant true
    tts_provider "xai"
    tts_voice "eve"
    stt_provider "xai"
    stt_model "xai-stt"
  end
end
